# Env Template Index
#
# Do not put real secrets in this file. Actual `.env`, `.env.local`, and
# `.env.backup-*` files are ignored by git and excluded from Docker build context.
#
# Local integrated run:
#   cp .env.local.example .env
#
# Production-like Docker compose or single-host deploy:
#   cp .env.prod.example .env
#
# Separated deployment units should use:
#   frontend/.env.local.example or frontend/.env.prod.example
#   backend/.env.local.example  or backend/.env.prod.example
#
# Runtime ownership:
# - Root `.env` is only a monorepo/local-compose umbrella env.
# - Frontend env may contain only browser-facing `VITE_*` values.
# - Backend env owns DB credentials, LLM provider keys, and runtime artifact config.
